<p>Across all of it, three rules matter most for a Cocker: <strong>weigh every meal</strong> (and count treats in the daily total) to keep a weight-prone breed lean; <strong>favour a clean named protein and grain-free recipe</strong> to protect those ears; and <strong>keep fat moderate</strong> given the pancreatitis tendency. Clean and dry the ears regularly alongside the diet — food is one half of ear health, hygiene the other. If ear trouble, itching, weight, coat condition or toileting changes noticeably and doesn't settle, book a vet check.</p>

